data.Unnamed: 1: Split volumes for VN Origin (This is now updated in V4 of the template)
Scope: All previous lanes from CN Origins to global destinations with the Shippers Quanta, Inventec and Tech-Front
Split factor:  All lanes involved will have volume spit of xx-xx percent.  Example: CKG-US IDS COMM 4 (xx%) and HAN-US IDS COMM 4 (xx%)
All impacted lanes will have a corresponding Award Segments based on the original lane set up.
The Number of Lanes:
We are tendering 813 lanes this RFQ (as of V4 of the bid template)
Any lanes awarded during the pre-award / Round 1 will be removed from subsequent rounds.
DIM Factor Updates:
Due to questionable cubic volume numbers received for the prior year shipments, we will use the same DIM factor as previous contract year.
- All A3 related lanes will be 1:7.
- All PTY-LA lanes will be 1:7.
- All ELF lanes will be 1:7.
- Most IDS related lanes will be ACTUAL, some of the larger ones that will be 1:7 include the Hunxe and Duiven lanes.
- The majority of CKG/PVG-xxx lanes will be ACTUAL.
- Lanes into TPE will be 1:7.
- Africa lanes (excluding some South Africa) will be 1:7.
- We matched up lane combinations associated with PRG & BUD, CAN & HKG, and SIN & JHB.
- Remaining new lanes (those not tendered last year) are based on the best available shipment information.
- The vast majority of the remaining lanes had no DIM change from last year, there were some adjustments based on best available shipment information.
TAT Changes:
There are some TAT changes for this year.  Please review the TAT for each lane & ST-SL and bring any concerns to our teams.
As normal - new lanes will have TAT's based upon similar existing lanes.
IDS lanes - this year we maintain the same grouping as of last year.
Volumes (and associated data) represent 12 month projected volumes for the 2025 RFQ contract period - June 1, 2025 to May 31, 2026:
- Tab F, columns N & O
- Tab G, columns O & P
- Tab H, columns Q, R, S & U

data.col_0: 2025 HP Air RFQ - Rate Entry Sheet Instructions:
The dim ratio calculation cannot be relied upon this year, thus it is not being included.  This may be due to questionable cubic centimeter volume numbers received for last year's shipments.
An estimated 1:6 DIM Ratio has been provided (note - 1.00 = less than or equal to 1.00).  We will be continue to review the cubic volume data to determine the cause of the issues.
HP will continue to use the 250 kilometer radius application.  Through the year, we have reviewed the ports in relation to our 250 km range and determined there were a few ports that
needed to be removed from this year's RFQ to better fit the rule.
Examples:  1) HGH is represented by PVG.  2) DTW, CMH & PIT are represented by CLE.  3) BWI & RDU are represented RIC.  4) PHL is represented by JFK.
o Extended Origin Pickup Fee SOUTH CHINA - these are to be associated with the Port Code CAN (Country Code CN/HK):

This fee is intended to cover the pickup trucking portion for extended origins for a door-to-door or door-to-airport move for the various destination cities in Southern China transiting via Hong Kong.
It is not an add-on to the HKG Origin Pickup Fee.  Instead it will be used as the stand alone Origin Pickup fee for extended origin points.
We do not accept additional fuel surcharges on these pickups.
HP will only have one extended pickup fee. This is listed as "South China" and is to cover origin cities such as Futian, Guangzhou, Huang Pu, Jiangmen, Longhua, Shenzhen, Shunde, Tai Shan,
Zhongshan, ZhuHai & Dongguan (list is not exhaustive).
This charge is to cover trucking and any other transaction based fees including EPZ outbound fees and border crossing fees. No additional pickup accessorial fees will be accepted.
In summary, ALL extended pickup associated costs must be included in the Extended Pickup Fee.  No other costs will be accepted.
o Extended Destination Delivery Fee SOUTH CHINA - these are to be associated with the Port Code CAN (Country Code CN/HK):

This fee is intended to cover the delivery trucking portion for extended destinations for a door-to-door or airport-to-door move for the various destination cities in Southern China transiting via Hong Kong.
It is not an add-on to the HKG Destination Delivery Fee.  Instead it will be used as the stand alone Destination Delivery Fee for extended destination points.
We do not accept additional fuel surcharges on these deliveries.
HP will only have one extended delivery fee. This is listed as "South China" and is to cover destination cities such as Futian, Guangzhou, Huang Pu, Jiangmen, Longhua, Shenzhen, Shunde, Tai Shan,
Tai Shan, Zhongshan, ZhuHai & Dongguan (list is not exhaustive).
This charge is to cover trucking and any other transaction based fees and border crossing fees.  No additional destination delivery accessorial fees will be accepted.
In summary, ALL extended destination delivery associated costs must be included in the Extended Delivery Fee.  No other costs will be accepted
Note:  the Lift rates and TAT's for HKG and CAN shipments must be the same, just the pickup and delivery rates can vary.
o Extended Origin Pickup Fees JOHOR BAHRU - these are to be associated with the Port Code JHB (Country Code MY/SG):

This fee is intended to cover the pickup trucking portion for extended origins for a door-to-door or door-to-airport move for the various destination cities in the Johor Bahru area transiting via SIN.
It is not an add-on to the SIN Origin Pickup Fee.  Instead it will be used as the stand alone Origin Pickup fee for extended origin points.
We do not accept additional fuel surcharges on these pickups.
HP will only have one extended pickup fee. This is listed as "Johor Bahru" and is to cover origin cities such as Johor Bahru, Bandar Baru Uda, Gelang Patah and Senai (list is not exhaustive).
This charge is to cover trucking and any other transaction based fees and border crossing fees. No additional pickup accessorial fees will be accepted.
In summary, ALL extended pickup associated costs must be included in the Extended Pickup Fee.  No other costs will be accepted.
o Extended Destination Delivery Fees JOHOR BAHRU - these are to be associated with the Port Code JHB (Country Code MY/SG):

This fee is intended to cover the delivery trucking portion for extended destinations for a door-to-door or airport-to-door move for the various destination cities in the Johor Bahru area transiting via SIN.
It is not an add-on to the SIN Destination Delivery Fee.  Instead it will be used as the stand alone Destination Delivery Fee for extended destination points.
We do not accept additional fuel surcharges on these deliveries.
HP will only have one extended delivery fee. This is listed as "Johor Bahru" and is to cover destination cities such as Johor Bahru, Bandar Baru Uda, Gelang Patah and Senai (list is not exhaustive).
This charge is to cover trucking and any other transaction based fees and border crossing fees.  No additional destination delivery accessorial fees will be accepted.
In summary, ALL extended destination delivery associated costs must be included in the Extended Delivery Fee.  No other costs will be accepted
Note:  the Lift rates and TAT's for SIN and JHB shipments must be the same, just the pickup and delivery rates can vary.
As usual - the provider may utilize the gateway of their choice that meets HP TAT and service level requirements.  Typical uplift port for CAN area is HKG, and for JHB area is SIN.
The Service Provider is expected to enter the pickup/lift/delivery rates in the three rate entry tabs (tabs F, G & H).
Calculated rates are provided in the Carrier Report tab (tab X).  Please ensure the calculated rates in tab X represent the bids you want to submit to HP.
Enter Pickup Rates in Columns H, I, J & K (or the total in just one of these columns)
Enter Decline in Column Q (P_Decline Column) if you decline to bid on the pickup service for an entire country
Error message will show up in Column R and corrections must be made until there are no more error message
Enter Delivery Rates in Columns H, I, J, K & L (or the total in just one of these columns)
Enter Decline in Column R (D_Decline Column) if you decline to bid on the delivery service for an entire country
Error message will show up in Column S and corrections must be made until there are no more error message
Enter Standard Lift Rates in Column K
Enter Expedited Lift Rates in Column L
Enter Decline in Column V (L_Decline Column) if you decline to bid on a specific lane
Error message will show up in Column W and corrections must be made until there are no more error message
Calculation of bid rates by lane (constructed from the rates input in the Pickup, Delivery and Lift tabs)
This report was designed to have a look similar to the HP Rate Card

If the word "ERROR" or "#VALUE" appears in column U, there is a problem that needs to be corrected.  There is something in the Pickup, Delivery or Lift tabs that is not allowing a complete bid to be calculated for a lane.
